HEADWORD: Zymogene
<hw>Zym"o*gene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Zyme</ets> +
root of Gr. <?/ to be born.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>One of a
physiological group of globular bacteria which produces fermentations of
diverse nature; -- distinguished from <xex>pathogene</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

